          <h2 style="font-weight:800;font-size:clamp(26px,3vw,36px);line-height:1.12;letter-spacing:-.025em;margin:0 0 18px">Most tools stop at storage and search. Doc&#8209;Salvage goes further.</h2>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.65;color:#52617A;margin:0 0 16px">Processing is what happens when your documents need to do something — not just sit in a folder, but actively feed into your business operations. AI agents read each document, extract the relevant information, and carry out the workflow a trained employee would — accurately, consistently, and without the manual effort.</p>
          <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #E7E1D4;border-left:3px solid #1772A8;border-radius:10px;padding:22px 24px">
            <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#1772A8;margin-bottom:10px">A simple example</div>
            <p style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.65;color:#3A4A60;margin:0">Your accounts team receives a supplier invoice. Instead of manually keying the details into your accounting system, you process it through Doc&#8209;Salvage. The AI agent reads the invoice, extracts the supplier name, amount, line items, and due date, then inserts it directly into your accounting system — ready for approval. The same logic applies to bank statements and receipts. The AI doesn't just file the document. <b style="color:#083A4D">It works it.</b></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:#06303F;border-radius:16px;padding:38px 34px;color:#fff;align-self:stretch">
          <h3 style="font-weight:800;font-size:22px;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin:0 0 16px">Why $1 per document?</h3>
          <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;color:#C4D6DF;margin:0 0 18px">Because processing isn't passive. Every $1 reflects real work carried out on your behalf — the kind of work that would otherwise land on your team's desk. You're not paying for the document to exist. You're paying for it to be acted on.</p>
          <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;color:#C4D6DF;margin:0 0 24px">And because each capability works independently, you only pay for Processing when you need it.</p>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px">
